- [http://www.DesignContest.com/ DesignContest.com]  Graphic design website where designers compete not only to win cash prizes, but also to advance in levels, earn points and receive medals.

- [http://Freerice.com Freerice.com]  Freerice is a non-profit website that is owned by and supports the United Nations World Food Programme. For each answer you get right, The World Food Programme gets 10 grains of rice. 

- Other Clicks for a Cause are [HungerSite](http://www.thehungersite.com): [Wikipedia writeup](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Hunger_Site) and [Nonprofits.com](http://www.thenonprofits.com/)

- [http://fold.it/portal/ FoldIt] is an application that allows users to collaborate together through collective intelligence to solve scientific problems that have thwarted researchers for decades.

- [http://eyewire.org/ Eyewire] is an application to map the brain by mapping the 3D structure of neurons and discovering neural connections.

- [http://phylo.cs.mcgill.ca/ Phylo] is a puzzle matching game that helps map diseases in DNA.

- [http://stackoverflow.com Stack Overflow].  Stack Overflow is a question and answer site for professional and enthusiast programmers. It's 100% free, no registration required. Answering questions earns you points and badges. You also earn points/badges for posting what others deem an interesting question.  A huge repository of programming problems and solutions has been crowd-sourced by compelling programmers to spend the time to help others and share their knowledge.

- [Duolingo](http://www.duolingo.com), [Ted Talk](http://www.ted.com/talks/luis_von_ahn_massive_scale_online_collaboration.html): Learn a language and help translate the web. Reviewed by [PCMag](http://www.pcmag.com/article2/0,2817,2402570,00.asp), [Fluent in 3 Months](http://www.fluentin3months.com/duolingo/), [Enterprise Gamification](http://enterprise-gamification.com/index.php/en/education-a-training/91-duolingo-how-gamified-language-learning-benefits-the-internet-and-humanity)

- [EatDifferent](http://www.eatdifferent.com/): Want to change your eating habits for the better?

- [Waze](http://www.waze.com/): What if you could find the quickest route to work and back, every day?

- [Why Crunching Data For Science Is the Future of Game-Playing](http://www.popsci.com/gadgets/article/2012-01/gamification-data)

- Barebones Design: Cowclicker on [Wired](http://www.wired.com/magazine/2011/12/ff_cowclicker/), Spinoff [Cowclicktivism](http://cowclicktivism.org/) donates cows through Oxfam

- [Global Crowd Intelligence](http://www.globalcrowd.com/gci/index.php/): Game to help the US Government Intelligence Service improve its predictions of world events.

- [PlayTheCity.nl](http://www.playthecity.nl) is a crowdsourcing game designed to make everyone in a city get involved in the planning phase of the city, by 'playing the city' game instead.
